librpip - A Library for Using Raspberry Pi Peripherals in Userland.

Documentation
-------------

Documentation is at http://librpip.frasersdev.net/documentation/
To get the most of of librpip you will need to configure the peripherals on your Raspberry P. See http://librpip.frasersdev.net/peripheral-config/ for details. Librpip will detect and use whatever hardware has been made available.


Installation
------------

Download the current release from http://librpip.frasersdev.net/get/download/

The Library installs into /usr/local/*. Edit the Makefile to install into other locations.

To build and install run the following
$ ./configure
$ make 
$ sudo make install

Then optionally make the examples
$ make examples



